-- Push filters early, use hash-based sampling instead of RAND()
WITH filtered_customers AS (
    SELECT customer_id, status
    FROM D_CUSTOMERS
    WHERE status IN ('N', 'F', 'I')  -- Pre-filter customers
),

filtered_raw AS (
    SELECT 
        RAW_MDS.*,
        filtered_customers.status
    FROM RAW_MDS
    INNER JOIN filtered_customers 
        ON RAW_MDS.customerId = filtered_customers.customer_id
    WHERE daysSinceFirstCompletedOrder BETWEEN -1e-12 and 1e-12  -- Direct equality check
),

deduplicated AS (
    SELECT 
        *,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY objectId 
            ORDER BY transactionDate
        ) AS dedup
    FROM filtered_raw
    WHERE status IN ('F', 'I')  -- Keep all F and I
       OR (status = 'N' AND MOD(ABS(HASH(objectId)), 100) < 50)  -- Deterministic 50% sample of N
)

SELECT * 
FROM deduplicated
WHERE dedup = 1
